A '''glyph''' consisting of a rune encrusted pendant was used amongst the society of the [[Bosph (species)|Bosph]] [[Species/Legends|species]] to claim ownership of an object. The only Bosph allowed such glyphs were those who were [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]], known as [[Ela b'Yentarr]], who also made up the entirety of the [[Bosph government|government]] on the Bosph [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of [[Bosph/Legends|Bosph]]. Any object that a glyph was placed upon was considered to be owned from that moment on by the owner of the glyph. If two Bosph both claimed ownership of an item they would duel for it, sometimes to the [[Death/Legends|death]]. All items not claimed with a glyph were considered equally owned by all members of Bosph society. The Bosph [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Bora Boru]] owned such a glyph and used it to claim his ship, the [[Bosphon Forever]].

